<item>
            <title>[LU-14310] Interop: sanity test 130g fails with  error &apos;failed to setstripe -C 700 /mnt/lustre/f130g.sanity&apos;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-14310</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;sanity test_130g fails for master, future 2.14.0, clients and older servers. sanity test 130g was added by 409719608cf0 &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11848&quot; title=&quot;filefrag/FIEMAP doesn&amp;#39;t work for PFL or FLR files&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-11848&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-11848&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; lov: FIEMAP support for PFL and FLR file to Lustre after the 2.13.57 tag. We need to skip this test if the server version is less than or equal to 2.13.57.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Looking at the suite_log for the failure at &lt;a href=&quot;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/6e4f8226-6269-4979-a03f-af7e98a714be&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;https://testing.whamcloud.com/test_sets/6e4f8226-6269-4979-a03f-af7e98a714be&lt;/a&gt;, we see&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;== sanity test 130g: FIEMAP (overstripe file) ======================================================== 02:39:48 (1608777588)
lfs setstripe: setstripe error for &apos;/mnt/lustre/f130g.sanity&apos;: Invalid argument
 sanity test_130g: @@@@@@ FAIL: failed to setstripe -C 700 /mnt/lustre/f130g.sanity 
  Trace dump:
  = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/test-framework.sh:6273:error()
  = /usr/lib64/lustre/tests/sanity.sh:12727:test_130g()
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
                <environment>Lustre client &amp;gt; 2.13.57 with Lustre servers &amp;lt;= 2.13.57</environment>
        <key id="62277">LU-14310</key>
